{"id":"227152963_Wild_McEliece","abstract":"The original McEliece cryptosystem uses length-n codes over F\n2\nwith dimension ≥ n − mt efficiently correcting t errors where 2m\n≥ n. This paper presents a generalized cryptosystem that uses length-n codes over small finite fields F\nq\nwith dimension ≥ n − m(q − 1)t efficiently correcting \\(\\lfloor{qt/2}\\rfloor\\) errors where q\nm\n≥ n. Previously proposed cryptosystems with the same length and dimension corrected only \\(\\lfloor{(q-1)t/2}\\rfloor\\) errors for q ≥ 3. This paper also presents list-decoding algorithms that efficiently correct even more errors for the same codes over F\nq\n. Finally, this paper shows that the increase from \\(\\lfloor{(q-1)t/2}\\rfloor\\) errors to more than \\(\\lfloor{qt/2}\\rfloor\\) errors allows considerably smaller keys to achieve the same security level against all known attacks.","authors":["Daniel J. Bernstein","Tanja Lange","Christiane Peters"],"meta":["March 2011","DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-19574-7_10","Conference: Proceedings of the 17th international conference on Selected areas in cryptography"],"references":["268161104_Algorithmic_number_theory_Lattices_number_fields_curves_and_cryptography_Reprint_of_the_2008_hardback_ed","228976029_Cryptanalysis_of_the_McEliece_cryptosystem_over_hyperelliptic_codes","226115302_Code-Based_Cryptography","221462135_Reducing_Key_Length_of_the_McEliece_Cryptosystem","221348198_Algebraic_Cryptanalysis_of_McEliece_Variants_with_Compact_Keys_2009_Secret_19","221327329_How_to_Achieve_a_McEliece-Based_Digital_Signature_Scheme","221327269_Security_Bounds_for_the_Design_of_Code-Based_Cryptosystems","220335351_Practical_Key_Recovery_Attacks_On_Two_McEliece_Variants","220334069_Compact_McEliece_Keys_from_Goppa_Codes","37446602_Cryptography_based_on_error_correcting_codes","3079390_A_New_Algorithm_for_Finding_Minimum-Weight_Words_in_a_Linear_Code_Application_to_McEliece's_Cryptosystem_and_to_Narrow-Sense_BCH_Codes_of_Length_511","312941065_Semanticall